Re: It will not be / It will be not
by Yudan Taiteki » Sat 08.08.2009 2:19 pm Since this is in the English practice section I'll point something else out (sorry if this is rude).This may be different by dialect so maybe others have different opinions. For me, the contraction of "I have" to "I've" is only done when it is being used as an auxiliary expressing present perfect. For instance:x I've five dollars. o I have five dollars.x I've to go to the store today. o I have to go to the store today.o I've seen that movie. o I have seen that movie.
-Chris Kern
Yudan Taiteki
