Re: It will not be / It will be not
by two_heads_talking » Mon 08.10.2009 8:56 am astaroth wrote:NileCat wrote:" He loves me, he loves me not..."And since we are here ... what about Fear you not which time to time I hear in tv shows or movies? (Though most of the time it is said in jest.)Usually a phrase such as "Fear you not" or "He loves me, he loves me not" or "What light through yonder window breaks?" are so commonly quoted that it becomes standard usage even though it might not be so standard. It's like pulling a phrase from a dictionary. On the surface, it looks completely normal, but underneath the surface lies monsters..
